## 1. Data Model

**Q: What fields are stored for each workout entry?**

The app uses multiple entity types organized hierarchically. The core entities and their fields are:

- **UserProfile**: id (number), name (string), createdAt (epoch ms)
- **Session**: id (number), date (string YYYY-MM-DD), startTime (epoch ms), endTime (epoch ms | undefined), duration (seconds | undefined), notes (string), templateId (number | undefined)
- **Activity**: id (number), sessionId (FK to Session), type (ActivityType: 'Strength' | 'Cardio' | 'Skill'), title (string), order (number), notes (string)
- **StrengthSet**: id, activityId (FK), setIndex (0-based), weight (kg), reps, rpe (1-10 | undefined), restSeconds (undefined), tempo (string | undefined), isCompleted (boolean)
- **CardioEntry**: id, activityId (FK), duration (seconds), distance (km | undefined), pace (string | undefined), avgHr (number | undefined), rpe (number | undefined)
- **SkillEntry**: id, activityId (FK), duration (seconds), rpe (number | undefined), notes (string), tags (string[])
- **ExerciseReference**: id, name, bodyPart, equipment, isCustom (boolean)
- **WorkoutTemplate**: id, name, activities (TemplateActivity[])

