## 2. Data Persistence

**Q: How is data stored?**

Data is stored in **IndexedDB** via the **Dexie.js v4.0.11** library. The database is named `WorkoutLogDB`.

Schema (v2):
- sessions: ++id, date, startTime, templateId
- activities: ++id, sessionId, type, title
- strengthSets: ++id, activityId, setIndex
- cardioEntries: ++id, activityId
- skillEntries: ++id, activityId
- exercises: ++id, name, bodyPart, equipment, isCustom
- templates: ++id, name
- userProfiles: ++id, name

Additionally, `localStorage` stores two flags: `workoutlog-guest` (guest mode) and `workoutlog-lang` (language preference en/zh).

**Q: Where is the storage logic implemented?**

- Database schema & instance: `src/db/database.ts`
- All CRUD operations (500+ lines): `src/db/operations.ts`
- Type definitions: `src/types.ts`

**Q: Is the app fully offline-capable?**

Yes. The app is **fully offline-first**:
- All data stored locally in IndexedDB — no backend API
- No network required — works 100% offline
- PWA with Service Worker (via vite-plugin-pwa) — installable on mobile
- No cloud sync — data is local-only by design

**Q: Is there any data migration or versioning logic?**

- Schema is at **version 2** (v2 added the `userProfiles` table). Dexie handles automatic database upgrades.
- On first launch, `seedExercisesIfEmpty()` in `src/db/database.ts` seeds ~50 default exercises (bilingual en/zh names) organized by body part.
- `getLastUsedDefaults(exerciseTitle)` provides smart default values (weight/reps/rpe/rest) from the most recent session for auto-fill.

